\b Description:\b0\par
\tab Mine Saga begins at Darkstone Mine, a completely dark mission \par
in which you have to use flares to navigate and light torches while\par
trying to complete your objectives. The next mission, Mine Affairs,\par
brings you to a small manor in the city that hides a mournful secret.\par
Bonds of Mine takes you to the northern mountains through a garrison,\par
a Hammerite Monastery with a dark past and an ancient mage's tower.\par
The last mission, Mine Saga's End, is set back in the city.\par
\tab For additional improved graphics, I recommend downloading and \par
installing the Thief Enhancement Pack by Nameless Voice.\par
\b\par
Author's Note:\b0\par
\tab Mine Saga is a compilation of all my previously released \par
missions, updated with better graphics, visuals, enhancements to \par
gameplay and many additions, changes, and improvements that I couldn't \par
possibly list. Mine Saga also includes a brand new unreleased mission, \par
briefings for each mission and an ending credits movie.\par
\tab Darkstone Mine was originally created in just a weekend, and was \par
intended to take an element of gameplay, flares, and use them to their \par
utmost potential. As a consequence, the entire mission has zero ambient \par
light and is contained in the space of a 64 foot cube.\par
\tab Mine Affairs was released just a week after Darkstone Mine was\par
released. It was originally intended to be in a 64 foot cube, but was\par
rearranged to better utilize space and fits in a 64x128x32 foot brush, \par
with the same volume.\par
\tab With Bonds of Mine, I tried to create a large organic feeling \par
outside environment using textures I personally made. Construction\par
took several months. It's the only mission in the campaign that wasn't\par
intended to fit in a 64 foot cube.\par
\tab Mine Saga's End is also a genuinely small mission that was\par
originally intended to be inside a 64 foot cube, but was just slightly\par
expanded for an very special effect and added visuals.\par
\tab I certainly hope you enjoy the missions, but most of all I hope I \par
get you thinking about some of the ideas and themes that are presented \par
through the story. It was those ideas that fueled the creation of all\par
my missions.\par
\par
Thanks for playing!\par
\par
-Michael A. Cleveland\par
